<H3> <TI>   Russia Protests U.S. Violation of Air Space </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Protests U.S. Violation of Air Space </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0806100494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0812 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0806100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 8 (XINHUA) -- Russia today lodged a 
protest with the U.S. Government against the violation of its 
air sovereignty by a U.S. civilian aircraft yesterday. 
  Russia's First Deputy Foreign Minister Anatoliy Adamishin 
summoned U.S. Ambassador Thomas Pickering today delivering a 
statement of the Russian Government on the violation. 
  A U.S. Lockheed C-130 plane, on its way from Frankfurt of 
Germany to Tbilisi of Georgia, penetrated Russia's air space 
over the Black Sea town of Adler at 13:54 Moscow time Tuesday, 
without making any application in advance, the ITAR-TASS NEWS 
SERVICE said. 
  After the plane ignored warnings from Russian ground 
stations 
and flew 80 kilometers deep into the Russian space, Russian 
military aircraft took off and forced it to land at the Adler 
airport at 14:10. 
  The Russian statement said Russia wishes the U.S. side would 
take all measures necessary to prevent the reoccurrence of such 
incidents. 
  The U.S. ambassador expressed gratitude for Russia's 
restraint in handling the incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

