<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rate of Price Increases Drop in Guangdong Capital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rate of Price Increases Drop in Guangdong Capital </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0706114394 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 1000 
GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0706114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, 4 Jun (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE)--According 
to sources in departments in charge of price administration in 
Guangzhou, the price index, which rose earlier this year, 
dropped by a wide margin recently. 
  The recent price index for Guangzhou City increased 17.5 
percent, which was 7.6 percentage points lower than last year's 
average. According to preliminary estimates from departments in 
charge of price administration, the index dropped nine percent 
or so in May, which was markedly lower than the average increase 
in prices in the first quarter of this year. The rising trend 
in the general level of retail commodity prices has slowed down. 
Retail prices of a number of nonstaple foodstuffs and 
industrial products for daily use are lower than in the same 
period last year. 
  In order to deal with such problems as the production of 
fake 
and inferior goods, reaping staggering profits, asking 
exorbitant prices, and monopolizing the market, and to 
standardize pricing behavior, from 6 June on, departments in 
charge of the commodity price inspection in the city will 
strengthen the administration of work encouraging sales at 
marked prices and will punish, in strict accordance with laws 
and regulations, units and individuals who do not sell 
commodities at marked prices in a standardized manner. The 
practice of unreasonable charges levied in the service sector 
will be punished according to provincial regulations on the 
administration of executive charges, state regulations on price 
administration, and other laws and regulations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

