<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Says China Willing To Cooperate With Britain </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Says China Willing To Cooperate With Britain </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0806050094 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in Chinese 1459 GMT 
7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0806050094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Wang Hui (3769 1920)] </F>
  [Text] Macao, 7 Jun (ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE)--Chen Ziying, 
deputy director of the State Council's Hong Kong and Macao 
Affairs Office, said here today that the British side is not 
cooperating in the political area but China will still cooperate 
as much as possible with the British side in other areas. The 
matter hinges on the British side. Concerning the talks on Hong 
Kong's new airport, he hopes that progress can be made and an 
important breakthrough achieved. 
  Chen Ziying said that regarding the Hong Kong question, 
China 
has always advocated Sino-British cooperation because it is 
conducive to Hong Kong's smooth transition. Although the 
British side is not cooperating in the political area he hopes 
that, in other areas, it will not repeat the methods used in the 
political area. In other areas, we will try our best to 
cooperate with the British side. China's attitude has always 
been clear and we have made efforts in this regard and the 
matter rests with the other side. 
  Talking about the issue of Hong Kong's new airport, Chen 
Ziying said that along with Hong Kong's economic development, a 
new airport should be built and everyone had identical views on 
this. He said: Concerning the issue of Hong Kong's new airport, 
we think that things should be done according to the regulations 
stipulated by the original Memorandum of Understanding on the 
Airport and no extra financial burdens should be created for the 
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region [SAR]. In order to 
protect the interests of Hong Kong residents, and in order not 
to create extra financial burdens for the Hong Kong SAR, we have 
negotiated with the British side. Concerning this question, the 
Chinese side has never raised any extra demands; we have only 
one thing to say: Act according to the Memorandum of 
Understanding on the Airport. 
  Chen Ziying said that China is positive and enthusiastic 
about the airport talks and hopes that the talks on the new 
airport make progress and an important breakthrough is achieved 
as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

