<H3> <TI>   Investigation of Crash, `Black Box' Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Investigation of Crash, `Black Box' Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Authorities Contact Victims' Families </H4>

<F P=102> OW0706160594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1537 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0706160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Xian, June 7 (XINHUA) -- China Northwest Airlines 
has contacted the families of the 13 passengers from outside the 
mainland who died in a plane crash near Xian yesterday. 
  The 146 passengers and 14 crew died when China Northwest 
Airlines passenger plane crashed 30 kilometers southeast of 
Xian. There were no survivors. 
  Of the passengers, four were from Italy, two from the United 
States, two from Britain, one from Switzerland, three from Hong 
Kong and one from Taiwan, with the rest all from the Chinese 
Mainland, according to airlines officials. 
  The officials said that the bodies of these passengers are 
being properly taken care of. 
  Police are now looking for the possessions of these 
passengers around the site of the crash in Xian's suburban 
Changan County. 
  The cause of the crash is still being investigated, but 
rescue teams have already recovered the "black box" containing 
the flight recordings, which is being analyzed, officials said. 

</TEXT>

