<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Meets Japanese Corporation Chairman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Meets Japanese Corporation Chairman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0706125594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1216 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0706125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 7 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng 
met here this afternoon with Seiji Tsutsumi, chairman of Saison, 
a Japanese corporation. 
  During the meeting in Zhongnanhai, Li expressed appreciation 
over the positive attitude the Japanese corporation had taken in 
developing economic cooperation between China and Japan. 
  After briefing the guests on China's current economic 
situation and relevant policies, the Chinese premier gave a 
detailed account of the basic characteristics of China's 
socialist market economy. 
  The Saison corporation, a leading Japanese firm in the 
fields 
of services and marketing, has now launched various joint 
centures in Beijing and Guangzhou as well as in Jiangsu Province 
since it started business cooperation with China in the 1970s. 

</TEXT>

