<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Engineering Academy Elects President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Engineering Academy Elects President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0706152994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1452 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0706152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 7 (XINHUA) -- Renowned Chinese atomic 
physicist Zhu Guangya was elected today as president of the 
newly-founded Chinese Academy of Engineering (CAE), one of 
China's two top scientific bodies, in a secret ballot at a 
general meeting of the CAE academicians. 
  The 69-year-old Zhu, also an academician of the Chinese 
Academy of Sciences, is a research fellow with the Commission of 
Science, Technology and Industry for National Defence. 
  He is also chairman of the Chinese Association for Science 
and Technology, a member of the Central Committee of the 
Communist Party of China and vice-chairman of National Committee 
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference. 
  Also at the meeting, Zhu Gaofeng, an expert in posts and 
telecommunications, Shi Changxu, a metal expert, Pan Jiazheng, a 
hydro-engineering expert, and Lu Liangshu, an agronomist, were 
elected vice-presidents. They are all academicians of the CAE. 

</TEXT>

