<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Urges Restraint on Nuclear Issue </H4>

<F P=102> OW0906094294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0929 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0906094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 9 (XINHUA) -- China hopes that the 
concerned parties to the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula 
should keep calm and restraint and not close the door for 
negotiations easily. 
  Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang made the remarks at 
a 
press conference held here this afternoon when asked to expound 
China's views on the latest developments on the issue. 
  China is very much concerned over the latest developments 
over the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula, Shen said, and 
hopes that all the directly concerned parties should make 
further efforts to start talks so as to seek a peaceful 
resolution of the issue. 
  He stated that the Chinese side advocates two basic targets 
in solving the issue, that is, to realize final denuclearization 
of the peninsula and to safeguard peace and stability there. 

</TEXT>

