<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Attacks Wang Juntao's `Activities' </H4>

<F P=102> HK0906103294 Hong Kong AFP in English 1015 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK0906103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 9 (AFP)--The Chinese Government on 
Thursday accused German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel and 
Danielle Mitterrand of exploiting dissident Wang Juntao to 
promote "political activities" against Beijing. 
  "Wang Juntao was allowed to go abroad to receive medical 
treatment," a foreign ministry spokesman said by phone. 
  "We are against anyone making use of Wang Juntao in any form 
to carry out political activities against the Chinese 
government." 
  Wang, 35, had been sentenced to 13 years in jail for his 
role 
in the 1989 pro-democracy movement, but was released last month 
on medical grounds and put aboard a plane for the United States. 
  He made a private trip to France to commemorate the fifth 
anniversary of the June 4 crackdown in Tiananmen Square, and met 
Mitterrand -- the wife of French President Francois Mitterrand 
-- who chairs a human rights group known as France-Liberte. 
  Wang met Kinkel in Bonn on Tuesday before heading back to 
the 
United States. 

</TEXT>

