<H3> <TI>   Approves Loan for Highway Construction </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Approves Loan for Highway Construction </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0806204394 Beijing XINHUA in English 2029 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0806204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Washington, June 8 (XINHUA) -- The World Bank 
approved a loan of 380 million U.S. dollars here today to 
support the national highway project in China. 
  The loan, the bank said, will be used to build the 340 
kilometer superhighway between Shijiazhuang and Xinxiang in 
central China, which is part of the divided, four-lane 
Beijing-Shenzhen expressway. 
  The part of highway supported by the bank, according to 
senior bank transport specialist Hatim Hajj, is one of the most 
heavily traveled corridors in China. 
  Highway traffic in China grew 14.1 percent between 1982 and 
1992. China is now planning to construct a 25,000 kilometer 
national highway system equivalent to the U.S. interstate 
system, the bank said. 
  Bank lending to the highway sector in China since 1981 
totals 
over one billion dollars. 

</TEXT>

