<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Cites U.S. Official on Haiti Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Cites U.S. Official on Haiti Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0806204694 Beijing XINHUA in English 2037 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0806204694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Washington, June 8 (XINHUA) -- The United States is 
determined to take further steps to restore democracy in Haiti, 
a special adviser to the U.S. President on Haiti said here today. 
  "Further steps will be taken in the coming days and weeks," 
said William Gray at a hearing of the House Committee on Foreign 
Affairs. 
  "No options have been excluded. Democracy in Haiti will 
prevail," Gray said, "neither we nor the Haitian people can long 
wait for this event." 
  He stressed that the U.S. interest requires the restoration 
of the democratic process in Haiti and the return of the 
duly-elected Haitian President Jean-Bertrand Aristide. 
  Asked if a military intervention in Haiti is imminent, Gray 
said that "it is not imminent, at this time, that any is being 
planned other than those diplomatic actions which have been 
stated." [sentence as received] 
  "Our policy right now is to continue to press with the 
international community on the sanctions" against Haiti, Gray 
added. 

</TEXT>

