  [Text] Beijing, June 8 (XINHUA) -- Hu Jintao, member of 
the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist 
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, met here here this 
afternoon with Chu Song-il, president of the Central Committee 
of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, and his 
party. 
  During the meeting, Hu recalled his visit to the Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) last July, saying that China 
and the DPRK are close, friendly neighbors, and that the 
traditional friendship between the two parties and countries has 
taken root among their peoples. 
  The Chinese party and government cherish the friendly 
cooperative relations between China and the DPRK, which has 
withstood the tests of time, Hu noted. 
  Under the current world situation, Hu said, consolidating 
and 
strengthening bilateral cooperation and friendship not only 
accords with the fundamental interests of two countries and the 
wills of the two peoples, but also is conducive to stability and 
peace in Asia and in the world at large. 
  Hu also briefed the DPRK visitors on China's reform, opening 
and modernization drive as well as Communist Party construction. 
  Ju expressed congratulations on China's achievements in its 
modernization drive. He said that strengthening exchanges and 
cooperation between his organization and the All-China 
Federation of Trade Unions (ACFTU) will promote the friendly 
relations between the DPRK and China and that such relations 
should be passed on from generation to generation. 
  The DPRK visitors arrived here yesterday as ACFTU guests. 

</TEXT>

