<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   NPC Delegation Meets With Russian Duma Leaders in Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NPC Delegation Meets With Russian Duma Leaders in Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0706023994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0224 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0706023994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 6 (XINHUA) -- Inter-parliamentary 
cooperation was the main topic discussed here today by leaders 
of the Russian State Duma (lower house) and China's National 
People's Congress (NPC). 
  Valentin Kovalev, deputy chairman of the Duma, met with the 
vice chairman of the NPC National Committee, Wang Guangying, 
head of the Chinese NPC delegation which had stopped over in 
Moscow on its way home from Malta. 
  The two also discussed political and economic matters. 
  Kovalev said that the Russian State Duma was satisfied with 
a 
recent visit to China by its Chairman Ivan Rybkin. 
  Briefing the NPC delegation on Russian current affairs, he 
added that the Chinese and Russian parliaments should now 
develop a friendly and business-like relaionship. 

