BFN 

  [Text] Beidaihe, June 5 (XINHUA) -- China signed a lease 
agreement for five Tu-154 airliners from Russia here today. 
  The agreement was signed between China Gongan Industrial 
Development Company and Nordex Group Ltd. -- a multinational 
corporation exploring business primarily in the former Soviet 
Union republics. 
  Rent totalling 29 million U.S. dollars will be paid in 
installments over five years. Afterwards China may take 
ownership of the jumbos. 
  Last year China rented passenger aircraft from Uzbekistan on 
wet lease, sharing profits with the lender. This time China can 
pocket all profits during the lease period. 

