<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Carries `Economic News in Brief' for 9 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Carries `Economic News in Brief' for 9 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0906022994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0114 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0906022994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 9 (XINHUA) -- Today's economic news in 
brief. 
<H5>  Guilin Attracts More Overseas Investment </H5>
  Guilin, a city known for its superb landscape in Guangxi 
Zhuang autonomous region, boasts 385 overseas-funded 
enterprises, 200 of which are industrial projects. The city's 
overseas investment has broadened from solely service industry 
to such industrial sectors as electronics, machinery, food 
processing and handicrafts. 
<H5>  Technological Activities Draw Guangzhou Residents </H5>
  Residents in Guangzhou, capital city of Guangdong Province, 
are very active in studying new technology as 610 such 
organizations have been established in the city, drawing over 
80,000 people to learn and exchange skills. This activity has 
paid off as development results turned out in these 
organizations produced 150 million yuan in economic returns last 
year. 
<H5>  Farmers Keen on Ecological Farming </H5>
  About 20,000 ethnic farmers in Gongcheng Yao Autonomous 
County have benefited from ecological farming as their per 
capita grain output and net income have both registered 
noticeable growth. Farmers here are planting trees and 
introducing solar energy to neighboring villages to improve the 
county's ecological structure. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

