<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing To Invest 1 Billion Yuan To Improve Highways </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing To Invest 1 Billion Yuan To Improve Highways </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0906042294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0317 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0906042294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guiyang, June 9 (XINHUA) -- China will invest 1 
billion yuan in highway projects in 21 provinces and autonomous 
regions in central and western China. 
  The funds will be issued as payments instead of relief funds 
to farmers for their work on highway construction projects in 
poverty-stricken areas. 
  Yang Zhong, deputy director of the leading group of the 
aid-the-poor projects under the State Council, recently noted at 
a conference in Guiyang that it is one of the measures taken by 
the central government to help improve communications conditions 
in poverty-stricken areas. 
  Since 1985, the departments of communications in the related 
provinces and autonomous regions have constructed about 150,000 
kilometers of highways in rural areas, including roads for farm 
machines. 
  The highways link more than 1,500 towns and 10,000 villages. 
  According to Yang, now there are still 1,700 townships and 
more than 17,000 villages in China which have no access to 
highways. 
  He said that most of the villages and townships are in the 
poverty-stricken regions in the central and western parts of the 
country. 
  He said that the construction of highways should be placed 
at 
the top of the economic development agenda in poverty-stricken 
regions. Such projects are expected to promote the growth of the 
market economy and break the isolation of the regions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

