<H3> <TI>   Li Peng, Li Lanqing Inscribe for Nanchang University </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng, Li Lanqing Inscribe for Nanchang University </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0806145594 Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1100 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0806145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the occasion of the first founding anniversary 
of Nanchang University, State Council Premier Li Peng and Vice 
Premier Li Lanqing wrote inscriptions for the university. 
Premier Li Peng's inscription reads: Raise the level of 
running a school and rejuvenate Jiangxi's economy. Vice Premier 
Li Lanqing's inscription reads: Bring the combined strong 
points into play, further improve teaching quality and the 
social benefit of running a school, and contribute to running 
well a new-type university. 
  Under the correct leadership of the provincial party 
committee and government and with the support of the State 
Education Commission, Nanchang University has achieved 
gratifying results in teaching, scientific research, production, 
and spiritual civilization building, and enhanced its overall 
management capability since its founding on 4 May last year. 
In the past year, the university has strengthened teaching 
reforms focusing on the credit, elimination, and rolling 
competetion systems, thus improving teaching quality. The first 
acceptance rate on the national English examination of 1992 
students increased from 47 percent scored before the merger of 
two schools to 64.98 percent. At the same time, the university 
has achieved initial results in expansion of key disciplines. 
It has become a pre-doctoral education unit with an additional 
unit of Ph.D. graduate students, two doctoral tutors, and nine 
units of students studying for a master's degree, thus ending 
the situation in which there has been not any unit of Ph.D. 
graduate students in Jiangxi for a long time. 

</TEXT>

